{
  "texts": [
    "After a discussion with the participants, we concluded that explicit reasoning in decision-making can strengthen users' perceptions of the system's transparency.",
    "Whenever a system is transparent, it is easier for users to identify biases.",
    "If I can deliver my feedback with meaningful interaction, I can be sure of the system's transparency and possibly will be able to see if the system is biased.",
    "I would like to have a non-biased system, or else it is a serious usage issue for me.",
    "Therefore, we can observe that social media users generally prefer to know the rationale behind any decision-making process."
  ]
}